bio: I am a CASAC with a bachelors degree in Psychology. I have been providing services with dual diagnosis populations for over 10 years. I believe on the importance of reinforcing a person strengths without overlooking their flaws to help achieve mental and emotional stability. I am a counselor who actively listens to patents, actively help patients achieve their goals, improve their mental and emotional health by focusing on redirecting their focus away from life difficulties, and negativities. On a personal note, I was born in New Jersey and half raised in Colombia and half raised in Miami, FL. I  moved form Miami, FL to NY state capital region in 2016. Best decision I have made so far.

bio:
Currently I am a Certified Peer Specialist at St. Joseph's Hospital PROS Program in Syracuse, NY.  This position has suited me well as it benefits from my strengths and lived experiences which have not all been positive.  My past includes untreated mental health, childhood/adult trauma and self-medication through addiction. It has led me to where I am in life today.  My previous work experience has been in corporate America which was monetarily good however kept me sick.  Today I can use my skills and experience to help others on their path and give hope by continuing to do well.

Also, I use my background in art, meditation, movement and mindfulness in helping others.

In addition, I am a Reiki Practitioner Level II and commercial photographer.

bio: Will is a NY Certified Peer Specialist for the Mobile Integration Team at the Capital District Psychiatric Center in Albany,NY. Prior to coming to work at CDPC, Will co-facilitated peer meet-up groups at the Clifton-Park Halfmoon Library and Healing Springs Recovery Center in Saratoga Springs, NY. Will was the co-host and creator of Above Ground Podcast, a weekly podcast about mental health from the peer-spective from 2019-2024. Will has also been involved with suicide prevention since 2016 as a volunteer of the Capital Region Chapter of the American Foundation for Suicide Prevention. Will served as a Board Member from 2019-2021 and continues his support and work with AFSP by working at events throughout the year.
